I"X<ol>
  <li>Cook the rice following directions. Set aside to cool.</li>
  <li>Meanwhile, combine the oil, lemon juice and sugar in a small jug. Season with salt and pepper.</li>
  <li>Combine the rice, chickpeas, tomato, cucumber, avocado, capsicum and pecans in a large bowl.</li>
  <li>Mix the Olive Oil, Lemon juice and Caster Sugar for the dressing and gently toss until just combined. Divide among serving dishes. Serve with the bread.</li>
  <li>Try serving this recipe as a side salad at your next barbecue - it works well with chargrilled chicken breasts and barbecued beef steaks.</li>
</ol>
